✅ Goal Recap
Use case:

CMDB CSV refreshed once per day
Deploy Datadog only on new servers
Avoid re-running on existing ones
Fully automated, safe, auditable


OPTION 1 (Recommended): Delta via Facts on Target Hosts
If Datadog is installed, the agent config file exists: /etc/datadog-agent/datadog.yaml
So:

New server → file missing → install
Existing server → file exists → skip 

1️⃣ Inventory remains CMDB‑driven (same as before)
ansible-playbook -i cmdb_inventory.py deploy_datadog.yml
2️⃣ Delta‑Aware Datadog Playbook
- name: Install Datadog agent only on new servers
  hosts: prod
  become: yes
  gather_facts: no
  serial: 500

  tasks:
    - name: Check if Datadog is already installed
      stat:
        path: /etc/datadog-agent/datadog.yaml
      register: datadog_installed

    - name: Install Datadog agent (new servers only)
      shell: |
        DD_API_KEY={{ datadog_api_key }} \
        DD_SITE={{ datadog_site }} \
        bash -c "$(curl -L https://s3.amazonaws.com/dd-agent/scripts/install_script.sh)"
      when: not datadog_installed.stat.exists

    - name: Ensure Datadog agent is running
      service:
        name: datadog-agent
        state: started
        enabled: yes
      when: datadog_installed.stat.exists or true

